<sup>News Please</sup>

news-please is an open source, easy-to-use news crawler that extracts structured information from almost any news website. 
It can recursively follow internal hyperlinks and read RSS feeds to fetch both most recent and also old, archived articles.
You only need to provide the root URL of the news website to crawl it completely. news-please combines the power of multiple state-of-the-art libraries and tools,
such as scrapy, Newspaper, and readability. news-please also features a library mode,which allows Python developers to use the crawling and extraction functionality 
within their own program.

***news-please extracts the following attributes from news articles. An examplary json file as extracted by news-please can be found here.***

-headline
-lead paragraph
-main text
-main image
-name(s) of author(s)
-publication date
-language

